<div id="review_2893515961" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2893515961" />
    <a title="Daniel Davalos" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52438479-daniel-davalos"><img alt="Daniel Davalos" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1513716032p2/52438479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2893515961?book_show_action=true">Jul 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel Davalos" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel Davalos" href="/user/show/52438479-daniel-davalos">Daniel Davalos</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781506413518" href="/book/show/28276767-the-freedom-of-a-christian-1520">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2893515961" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14348244262635127172">What struck me most is Luther’s pastoral tone. Despite his reputation for irascibility, he shows great concern for the common, uneducated people, and reserves his harsh indictments for the Roman clergy. I have some issues with hints of two kingdom theology, but Luther is easy to read and very edifying.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

